  "body": "```erigon version 2022.08.1-alpha-7dabdc32```\r\n\r\nMy nimbus consensus client is not working when connected to Erigon on Goerli. It was fine up until the merge.\r\n\r\nErigon logs show a ton of\r\n\r\n```\r\nAug 11 15:45:57 erigon[2521290]: [WARN] [08-11|15:45:57.857] Served                                   conn=127.0.0.1:55930 method=engine_forkchoiceUpdatedV1 reqid=640 t=9.48µs err=\"the method engine_forkchoiceUpdatedV1 does not exist/is not available\"\r\nAug 11 15:45:57 erigon[2521290]: [WARN] [08-11|15:45:57.867] Served                                   conn=127.0.0.1:55932 method=engine_newPayloadV1 reqid=641 t=12.319µs err=\"the method engine_newPayloadV1 does not exist/is not available\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nand blocks are stuck on \r\n\r\n```\r\nAug 11 16:03:17 erigon[2522110]: [INFO] [08-11|16:03:17.116] [txpool] stat                            block=7382818 pending=10000 baseFee=0 queued=16382 alloc=880.1MB sys=1.3GB\r\n```\r\n\r\nHow to break this deadlock?\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
